&quot; I disagree with what you are saying , but I wll defend to the death your right to say it ... &quot; <br>
This quote is the core of my life view.<br>
I believe that each person is entitled to self-determination. <br>
If you want to be a hero , yo ucan do it , but by the same token if you wish to be a loser .. it's all good. <br>
I am in the unique position of being a black man educated in not only the South , but at Robert E. Lee Memorial Military Academy for Boys ... where in 5th grade each student recieves a course known as &quot; Corrective History&quot;<br>
You learn things like Lee was asked to lead the norths armies , but declined only when Virginia seceeded , because he was a loyal Virginian... true<br>
He never owned slaves .. lies <br>
The land that is Arlington Nat'l Cemetary was &quot;donated&quot; by the Lee's after the war ended ... lies .. it was ANNEXED by the North<br>
Virginia only seceeded because the were afraid of rumors that Maryland was going to seceed leaving them trapped between 2 southern states ... lies .. maryland declared for the North MONTHS before Virginia's secession.<br>
As for the Flag .. this is going to sound strange coming from a Military man .. but it is a symbolONLY if you let it be ... it can be a piece of cloth as Joril said , or it can be an icon of something you believe in .. and like i said .. wether or not I think you are right .. i will never allow anyone to take away your right to THINK that way ... its the same thing as in love ... would you want someone to love you because they see nothing else and have no other options , or because they have seen the length and the breadth of the world and find your particular sum total to be greater than all others ?<br>
It is important to me that ALL people be allowed to field their own viewpoints .. so that children can grow up and be exposed to all facets of the world , and then when they make a decision to be good people , it will come from themselves .. their core and their worldview .. not &quot; because I said so ! &quot;<br>
A single option is not a choice ... <br>
So no matter what the flag means to them ... I support their right to wave it proudly ... <br>
That said however .. when yo uwork FOR someone you have to abide by the rules they set forth .. first amendment rights can get yo fired .. it is your employers place , if the flag offends him .. its gotta go .. end of story .. it is as much his right to kee[p the flag out of his place as it is your right to wave it ... and I will fight tooth and nail &lt; the main reason for joining the military actually&gt; to be sure that no one ever takes away your right to wave the flag , or his/her right to ask you to keep it out of their place <br>
